content:
Using CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud requires the appropriate licenses, org and user account setup, and permissions assigned to user accounts.

License Requirements:

* CRM Analytics Plus license or CRM Analytics Growth license
* Data Cloud license

Enable CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud:
Set up Data Cloud in your Salesforce org.
Assign Users Data Cloud Permission sets.
Assign Users CRM Analytics Permissions.
Select the CRM Analytics Plus User or CRM Analytics Growth User permission sets for users to view data insights in CRM Analytics Direct Data.
Enable the Create and Edit CRM Analytics Dashboards permission for users to build dashboards and create insights in CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud.

Direct Data for Data Cloud Limits:
Query Limits:
* Maximum concurrent queries per tenant: See Data Cloud API Limits
* Maximum number of API queries and SQL queries: See Connect REST API Limits.
title: Setup and Requirements for CRM Analytics Direct Data for Data Cloud
